						<div class="postbody">I've also thought about this, but never tried to do anything like it (I don't have 3D modelling skills either).<br /><br />In the same vein, using 2D skeletal animation for an NES game might be interesting area to explore as well. Of course the results would have to be &quot;baked&quot; into prerendered sprites. 2D skeletal animations can be made with e.g. Spine (commercial software, <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://esotericsoftware.com/">http://esotericsoftware.com/</a><!-- m -->). Since Spine and other tools like it aren't designed for pixel graphics, it might be hard to get a good preview of the results. It might be best if something like RotSprite could be coupled with it.</div>

					
